Plug-in name: Callgraph
Plug-in shortname: cg
Description:
automatically compute the callgraph of the program. Using Eva might improve the precision of this plug-in

Most options of the form '-cg-option-name' and without any parameter
have an opposite with the name '-cg-no-option-name'.

Most options of the form '-option-name' and without any parameter
have an opposite with the name '-no-option-name'.

Options taking a string as argument should preferably be written
-option-name="argument".

***** LIST OF AVAILABLE OPTIONS:

-cg <filename>      dump the callgraph to the file <filename> in dot format
-cg-function-pointers  when Eva has not been computed, safely
                    over-approximate callees in presence of function
                    pointers; always done when Eva has been previously
                    computed. (set by default, opposite option is
                    -cg-no-function-pointers)
-cg-roots <s>       if not empty, display only the functions of the callgraph
                    reachable from the given functions (preferably use
                    -cg-roots="")
-cg-service-roots <s>  when computing callgraph services (see -cg-services),
                    use the given functions (and their immediate children) as
                    service roots. If none, use the main function if any;
                    else use every uncalled function (preferably use
                    -cg-service-roots="")
-cg-services        compute and display services (groups of related functions
                    which seem to provide common functionalities) from the
                    callgraph (set by default, opposite option is
                    -cg-no-services)
-cg-uncalled        add the uncalled functions to the callgraph (the main
                    function is always added anyway) (set by default,
                    opposite option is -cg-no-uncalled)
-cg-uncalled-leaf   add to the callgraph the uncalled functions that,
                    themselves, do not call any function (opposite option is
                    -cg-no-uncalled-leaf)

*** DEBUG

-cg-debug <n>       level of debug for plug-in Callgraph (default to 0)

*** GETTING INFORMATION

-cg-help            help of plug-in Callgraph
-cg-h               alias for option -cg-help

*** OUTPUT MESSAGES

-cg-log <K_1:file_1,...>  copy log messages from Callgraph to a file. <K> is
                    a combination of these characters:
                    a: ALL messages (equivalent to 'dfiruw')
                    d: debug       e: user or internal error (same as 'iu')
                    f: feedback    i: internal error
                    r: result      u: user error    w: warning
                    An empty <K> (e.g. ":file.txt") defaults to 'iruw'. One
                    plug-in can output to several files and vice-versa.
                    (preferably use -cg-log="K_1:file_1,...")
-cg-msg-key <k1[,...,kn]>  enables message display for categories
                    <k1>,...,<kn>. Use -cg-msg-key help to get a list of
                    available categories, and * to enable all categories
                    (preferably use -cg-msg-key="k1[,...,kn]")
-cg-verbose <n>     level of verbosity for plug-in Callgraph (default to 1)
-cg-warn-key <k1[=s1][,...,kn[=sn]]>  set warning status for category <k1> to
                    <s1>,...,<kn> to <sn>. Use -cg-warn-key help to get a
                    list of available categories, and * to enable all
                    categories. Possible statuses are inactive, feedback,
                    warning, error, abort, feedback-once, warning-once,
                    error-once. Defaults to warning. (preferably use
                    -cg-warn-key="k1[=s1][,...,kn[=sn]]")
